A terrifying whip-like tail slammed down onto the ground, flipping Nixi over. She noticed the tail swaying wildly, but it didn't seem to be targeting her. Nixi barely made out the monster roaring, scratching at the shadow it had created with its claws. Something was shifting through the darkness, poised to strike the monster.
<s>Suddenly, a gunshot pierced the air, and the monster instantly fell quiet, lying still on the ground. The surrounding darkness dissipated, revealing the truth of the situation. Kayer stood on the monster's body, holding a rifle, breathing heavily.
<s>“That was… one of the strangest Shadow Jumps I've ever done… Tan-to Kart Oron…” Kayer panted. For some reason, his eyes flashed with black light, and dark energy surged within him. But as soon as Kayer started speaking, his organic armor returned to its normal color, and his eyes turned back to their usual yellow.
<s>A few moments later, Nischi understood what had happened. They all knew that Kayer possessed eerie Shadow abilities, but he seldom used them because most people believed this ability was very evil and terrifying. However, Nischi didn't know that Kayer could use this ability in any darkness, nor did she realize how surprised Kayer himself seemed to be.
<s>“Are you alright?” Nischi couldn’t help asking.
<s>“I’m fine. I killed that thing, and I’ll be back to myself soon.” Kayer glanced at his “masterpiece,” and then Tenuk landed beside him, reverting to his original Spartus form.
<s>Now, the monsters were no longer moving, allowing them to have a good look at what it was. Its skin was dark and glossy, covered in a sticky liquid that clung tightly to the monster's body.
<s>Before Tenuk and Kayel could ask what this strange creature was, a monster emerged screaming from nearby bushes. At this moment, a familiar car crashed into the side of the monster, causing it to slide for a distance before stopping at Nisi's feet. Nisi didn't hesitate, grabbing the shotgun and shooting the monster's head, killing it instantly.
<s>"Ouch..." Rhetvik muttered from the driver's seat, then clumsily turned off the engine and got down from the truck. "Uh, I didn't mean to. Are you all right?"
<s>"You missed all the fun!" Tenuk said, shaking his head. "Where did you go?"
<s>"It's your fault for leaving me behind. I tried my best to catch up..." Rhetvik sighed. "May I ask, what are these terrifying things?"
Revtvik's question was answered by Sassarin, who had already stood up. He was covered in wounds and scratch marks, looking a bit dizzy, but his injuries didn't seem serious.
"You killed the Corrupter! Those infected monsters. When corruption attacked your god, these creatures were left behind."
"You mean… we… helped kill the terrifying monster god?" Tenuk stammered.
"Yes, that's right. There might be more Corrupters. But I couldn't shoot them in the head. I don't have a gun. And it wouldn't be fair for two against one, would it?" Sassarin walked up to Cayel and patted his head. "Thank you, little guy. You remind me of my old friend Arkady. Except you're not as ruthless, nor do you have the power to destroy the universe."
